text: Tan Eng Bock (29 April 1936 - 30 November 2020) was a Singaporean water polo player He competed in the men's tournament at the 1956 Summer Olympics. Tan died in Singapore on 30 November 2020 at the age of 84. ==References== Category:1936 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Olympians for Singapore Category:Water polo players
